==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dentilingual
<hw>Den`ti*lin"gual</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dens</ets> tooth + E. <ets>lingual</ets>.]</ety> <def>Produced by
applying the tongue to the teeth or to the gums; or representing a sound
so formed.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A dentilingual sound or
letter.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The letters of this fourth, <qex>dentilingual</qex> or
linguidental, class, viz., d, t, s, z, l, r.</q> <rj><qau>Am.
Cyc.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dentiloquist</ent>⟦br⟧
